<subSubSection id="1EF421CCFFB2C112FF37DD8EFE927E64" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="56517247FFB2C112FF37DD8EFB8F7F29" blockId="40.[151,1437,151,1257]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FF37DD8EFECD78B9" bold="true" box="[199,315,979,1005]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FEB3DD8EFD1478BA" authority="(Zahniser)" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zahniser" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[323,738,979,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasileira">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FEB3DD8EFD9378B9" box="[323,613,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Paraclorindaia brasileira</emphasis>
(Zahniser)
</taxonomicName>
is removed from 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FC5BDD8EFBD078B9" box="[939,1062,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FC5BDD8EFBD078B9" box="[939,1062,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here based on the refined definition of 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FF1DDDAAFE9E7F45" box="[237,360,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FF1DDDAAFE9E7F45" box="[237,360,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the description of the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FCD3DDAAFC267F45" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[803,976,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FCD3DDAAFC267F45" box="[803,976,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Paraclorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FC10DDAAFB9A7F45" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zahniser" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[992,1132,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasileira">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FC10DDAAFB9A7F45" box="[992,1132,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">P. brasileira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the ocelli close to the anterior margin of the head, anterior margin of the head not carinate, male pygofer with several macrosetae, and male pygofer with posteroventral claw, which justifies removal from 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FC50DA62FBED7F0D" box="[928,1051,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FC50DA62FBED7F0D" box="[928,1051,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and placement in 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FB19DA62FA607F0D" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[1257,1430,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FB19DA62FA607F0D" box="[1257,1430,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Paraclorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two genera share the texture of the frontoclypeus which is mostly smooth and shiny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56517247FFB2C112FF37DADAFA837FBD" blockId="40.[151,1437,151,1257]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FF37DADAFEB47FF5" box="[199,322,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FF37DADAFEB47FF5" box="[199,322,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(three members included in the phylogenetic analysis here) was resolved as monophyletic, but its relationship to other genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FDE5DAF6FD917F91" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[533,615,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Faltala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FDE5DAF6FD917F91" box="[533,615,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Faltala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group was not clear. Based on the smooth and shiny texture of the frontoclypeus and some similarity in the color pattern of the crown, it may be most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFB2C112FB31DA92FA987FBD" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[1217,1390,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraclorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFB2C112FB31DA92FA987FBD" box="[1217,1390,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Paraclorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
